# OpenShift Deployment Conventions

## Namespace

All resources deploy to `upstream-pulse`. Manifests use Kustomize (`oc apply -k deploy/openshift`).

## Resource Order

ConfigMap ‚Üí Postgres ‚Üí Redis ‚Üí Backend ‚Üí Worker ‚Üí Frontend (with OAuth proxy).

## Labels

All resources use standard Kubernetes labels:

```yaml
labels:
  app.kubernetes.io/name: <component>
  app.kubernetes.io/part-of: upstream-pulse
  app.kubernetes.io/component: <component>
```

## Images

- Manifests use placeholder `DEPLOY_REGISTRY/upstream-pulse/<component>:latest`.
- `deploy.sh` replaces at deploy time via `oc set image`.
- Internal registry: `image-registry.openshift-image-registry.svc:5000/upstream-pulse/<component>`.
- Postgres: `postgres:16-alpine` (pushed to internal registry).
- OAuth proxy: `quay.io/openshift/origin-oauth-proxy:4.16`.

## Non-Root

No `securityContext` in manifests ‚Äî enforced at image level. Both backend and frontend Dockerfiles use `USER 1001`. Init containers set `HOME=/tmp`.

## Resource Limits

| Component | CPU req/limit | Memory req/limit |
|-----------|--------------|-----------------|
| Backend | 100m / 500m | 256Mi / 512Mi |
| Worker | 100m / 500m | 256Mi / 512Mi |
| Frontend (nginx) | 50m / 200m | 64Mi / 128Mi |
| OAuth proxy | 10m / 100m | 32Mi / 64Mi |
| Postgres | 100m / 500m | 256Mi / 512Mi |
| Redis | 50m / 250m | 64Mi / 256Mi |

## Probes

- **Backend**: liveness `GET /health:3000`, readiness `GET /ready:3000`.
- **Frontend**: liveness/readiness `GET /healthz:8080`.
- **OAuth proxy**: `tcpSocket:4180`.
- **Redis**: liveness/readiness `exec redis-cli ping`.
- **Postgres**: `exec pg_isready -U postgres`.

## Environment Variables

- **Secrets** (`oc create secret`, not in git):
  - `postgres-credentials`: `POSTGRES_USER`, `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `POSTGRES_DB`
  - `upstream-pulse-secrets`: `GITHUB_TOKEN`, `GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY`, `JWT_SECRET`, `GITHUB_TEAM_TOKEN`
- **ConfigMap** (`upstream-pulse-config`): `NODE_ENV`, `PORT`, `LOG_LEVEL`, `PROMETHEUS_ENABLED`, `GITHUB_TEAM_ORG`
- **Derived**: `DATABASE_URL` built from secret vars in the manifest.

## Volumes

- `postgres-data` PVC (5Gi) ‚Üí `/var/lib/postgresql/data`
- `redis-data` PVC (1Gi)
- OAuth proxy TLS and cookie secrets (readOnly mounts)

## Deploy Script

`deploy.sh` is **user-run only** ‚Äî the agent must not execute it. Commands:

- `build` ‚Äî Docker images (linux/amd64)
- `push` ‚Äî Push to OpenShift registry
- `apply` ‚Äî `oc apply -k` + ConfigMap patch + set images + rollout
- `status` ‚Äî Show pods, services, routes
- `logs [component]` ‚Äî Tail logs
- `deploy` ‚Äî Full cycle (build + push + apply)

## Rules

- Never commit secrets. Use `oc create secret` per `secrets.example.yaml`.
- Postgres uses `Recreate` strategy (single PVC, no rolling update).
- Worker shares the backend image; only the command differs (`node dist/worker.js`).
- Frontend uses `serviceAccountName: frontend-proxy` for OAuth sidecar.
- Init container `db-migrate` runs before the backend starts.
